law.history: Repealed 1974 Ky. Acts ch. 114, sec. 25. -- Created 1952 Ky. Acts ch. 58, sec. 30, effective March 5, 1952.

metadata.catchline-at-repeal: Nonliability of state, its political subdivisions, agents or representatives for injury or property damage -- Nonliability for death or injury resulting from blackout or other precautionary measures.
